# HTTP Method Manipulation Notes

## Overview
HTTP Method Manipulation occurs when a web application improperly handles different HTTP methods such as GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, or OPTIONS.

This can sometimes lead to:
- Authentication bypass
- Access control issues
- Open redirection
- Unexpected application behavior

---

# Common HTTP Methods

| Method | Purpose |
|---|---|
| GET | Retrieve data |
| POST | Submit data |
| PUT | Update resources |
| DELETE | Delete resources |
| OPTIONS | Show allowed methods |
| PATCH | Partial updates |

---

# Basic Testing Workflow

## Change Request Method

Example:
- GET → POST
- POST → GET

Observe:
- Response changes
- Access control behavior
- Redirect handling
- Error messages

---

# Example Test Request

```http
POST /admin HTTP/1.1
Host: example.com
```

Try changing to:

```http
GET /admin HTTP/1.1
Host: example.com
```

